        <p>Nobody in the appliance repair industry talks about what fire seasons do to luxury appliances in communities like Agoura Hills. We're going to, because our technicians deal with the consequences every fall.</p>

        <p>Sub-Zero refrigerators, Wolf ranges, and Thermador units are engineered to last 20+ years with proper maintenance. The single biggest threat to that lifespan in the Agoura Hills and Conejo Valley foothills isn't use — it's particulate accumulation. The condenser coils on a Sub-Zero refrigerator are designed to be cleaned annually. In the foothill fire corridor, they need attention every 6 months during active fire seasons, and immediately after any significant smoke event in the area.</p>

        <p>A packed condenser coil forces the compressor to overwork. The compressor is the most expensive component in a Sub-Zero — a replacement can run $800–$1,200 for the part alone. A $200 coil cleaning prevents it. We'll always tell you honestly if we think preventive maintenance is worth it for your specific unit and location.</p>

        <p>The other Agoura Hills pattern is dryer vent accumulation. Canyon homes that back up to brush often have longer vent runs, and the combination of lint, ash, and dry conditions creates a genuine fire hazard. We inspect dryer vents on every dryer call in the Agoura Hills area and tell you the truth about what we find.</p>

